import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', bins=20)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.boxplot(data['distance'])
    plt.title('What is the average distance of flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Distance')
    plt.axvline(data['distance'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['distance'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    # Combine origin and destination airports
    airports = pd.concat([data['origin'], data['destination']])
    
    # Count the number of flights for each airport
    airport_counts = airports.value_counts().reset_index()
    airport_counts.columns = ['airport', 'count']
    
    # Create the bar chart
    chart = sns.barplot(x='airport', y='count', data=airport_counts)
    
    # Rotate x-axis labels if necessary
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(rotation=90)
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title("Which airports have the highest number of flights?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month
    sns.countplot(x='month', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flights by month?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
